    {
      "id": "github-demo-instructions",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Instructions",
      "position": { "x": 220, "y": 90 },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Demo\n\n1) Open **Document Properties** (top toolbar) → **GitHub**.\n2) Click **Sign In With GitHub**.\n3) Select an **Installation** (this is the GitHub App installation that grants repo access).\n4) Pick a repo (or type `owner/name`) and set **File path in repo**.\n5) Click **Commit Via GitHub App**.\n6) Copy the new address from the URL bar: `github://owner/repo/path/to/file.node`.\n7) Paste that address into the address bar to validate loading.\n\nExpected:\n- [ ] Commit succeeds\n- [ ] Reload from `github://...` works\n- [ ] The graph stays editable after reload"
      }
    }
